    <Instrument_Host>
        <name>Venera 13</name>
        <type>Spacecraft</type>
        <description>

The Venera 13 spacecraft, like its sister craft Venera 14, comprised two
parts, a flyby carrier bus (flight platform) and an attached lander probe to
study Venus. The flight platform had instruments to study solar-wind
composition, gamma-ray bursts, ultraviolet radiation, and the electron
density of the ionosphere of Venus.

        </description>
